Problem 1. 
Outside  of  their  hum-drum  duties  as  6.042  LAs,  Oscar  is  trying  to  learn  to  levitate  using  only 
intense concentration and Liz is trying to become the world champion ﬂaming torch juggler.  Sup­
pose that Oscar ’s probability of success is 1/6, Liz’s chance of success is 1/4, and these two events 
are independent. 

(a)  If at least one of them succeeds, what is the probability that Oscar learns to levitate? 

(b)  If at most one of  them succeeds, what  is  the probability  that Liz becomes  the world ﬂaming 
torch juggler champion? 

(c)  If exactly one of them succeeds, what is the probability that it is Oscar? 

